    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 AC/1–2352</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by <persName corresp="#p_BATTLELC1" type="from"
                            >Lucius D. Battle</persName>, Special Assistant to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d5fn1">This memorandum was directed to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BARNESRG1">Barnes</persName> (<gloss target="#t_SS1"
                            >S/S</gloss>) for action by <persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1"
                            >Perkins</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>) and for the
                        information of <persName corresp="#p_BYROADEHA1">Byroade</persName> (<gloss
                            target="#t_GER1">GER</gloss>) and <persName corresp="#p_MATTHEWSHF1"
                            >Matthews</persName> (<gloss target="#t_G1">G</gloss>). The points
                        covered in this memorandum were also made in Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName>’s memorandum of his
                        conversation with <persName corresp="#p_FRANKSSOS1">Franks</persName>, not
                        printed. (396.1/1–2452)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-24">January 24,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_FRANKSSOS1">Sir Oliver Franks</persName> left with the
                    Secretary this morning the attached message from Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName>. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1"
                        >Acheson</persName> asked whether the message we had from the British
                        yesterday<note n="2" xml:id="d5fn2">Presumably the reference here is to
                            <persName corresp="#p_PERKINSGW1">Perkins</persName>’ memorandum for the
                        record, Jan. 23, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> which suggested that
                    the <pb facs="0049" n="5" xml:id="pg_5"/> quadripartite meeting be held in
                    London before the Lisbon meeting changed this message. <persName
                        corresp="#p_FRANKSSOS1">Sir Oliver</persName> said that that message did not
                    change this one and that they had in fact been sent together. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> is, therefore, hoping that the
                    Secretary will come to London before the Lisbon meeting (for the quadripartite)
                    as well as after the Lisbon meeting.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName> would like to have some
                    thought given to the question of whether he should do this. He does not want to
                    get in a position of giving too much attention to the British and too little to
                    the other countries.</p>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">[Attachment]</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Personal Message From Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENSA1" type="from">Eden</persName> to Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1" type="to">Acheson</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>You will remember that I told you in Washington how much I hoped that you
                        would be able to spend a few days in London after the Lisbon meeting of the
                        North Atlantic Council.</p>
                    <p>I look forward very much to welcoming you here after the Lisbon meeting and
                        hope that this visit will fit in with your other plans and commitments.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1952-01-23">23rd January 1952</date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
